summary: This document is an email chain from October 2019 regarding FBI travel approval for agents to travel to Florida for the Epstein investigation. The purpose is to attend a victim briefing in Miami and conduct victim and witness interviews in Miami, West Palm Beach, and Palm Coast. It shows the logistical planning for investigative activities.

events.title: Planned Travel for Epstein Victim Briefing and Interviews
events.description: FBI agents from New York planned to travel to Florida to attend a victim briefing in Miami and conduct victim and witness interviews in Miami, West Palm Beach, and Palm Coast.

keyFacts: The FBI's Crimes Against Children and Human Trafficking Unit was actively investigating Epstein in October 2019, after his death.
Investigative activities included a planned victim briefing and multiple victim/witness interviews across Florida.
The travel request involved four agents with a total estimated cost of $6,263.50.
The document references case number 31E-NY-3027571 in relation to the travel.
The email chain shows coordination between FBI field offices (NY) and headquarters units for investigative travel approval.
